article.headline: Arkansas State 82, Valparaiso 61
article.story:
MINNEAPOLIS (AP) -- Ali Carter scored 22 points, 16 in the first
half, to lead Arkansas State to a 82-61 win over Valparaiso in the
third-place game of the Subway Classic in Minneapolis.

Zanet Lane scored 15 and Adrianne Davie added 14, as the Indians
(1-1) made 10 of 20 from three-point range to win their first game
of the season.

Jenna Stangler led Valparaiso (0-2) with 15 points. Katie Boone
had 11 for the Crusaders.

After getting off just five shots in the game's first seven
minutes, Valparaiso caught fire, erasing an early 10-point deficit
to take a 32-30 lead late in the first half on a free throw by
Stangler.

The Indians then went on a 10-0 run, scoring the first six
points of the second half, to take a 40-32 lead. Amber Abraham's
three-pointer with 12:07 remaining extended Arkansas State's lead
to 55-42.
